### 3. Async Generation Architecture (Missing — THE #1 UX Gap)

**Current problem:** [qwen_engine.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/Resound-Studio/apps/api/engines/qwen_engine.py) methods are all synchronous `def generate_speech()`. This blocks the FastAPI event loop.

**What VoiceBox does:** All heavy ops wrapped in `asyncio.to_thread()` — model loading, prompt creation, and audio generation all run in thread pool.

**What to implement:**
- Wrap all `engine.generate_speech()`, `engine.clone_voice()`, `engine.load()` calls in `asyncio.to_thread()`
- Convert [main.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/backend/main.py) endpoints from sync to async where they call engines
- Add `asyncio.create_task()` for background model downloads
- Add progress tracking via [utils/progress.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/backend/utils/progress.py)

**Impact:** Server never freezes during generation. Multiple users can use the API simultaneously.

---

