**Current problem:** Resound is CUDA-only. `torch.cuda.empty_cache()` is hardcoded everywhere. Zero Mac support.

**What VoiceBox does:** Dual backends — [mlx_backend.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/backend/backends/mlx_backend.py) for Apple Silicon (4-5x faster via Metal), [pytorch_backend.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/backend/backends/pytorch_backend.py) for Windows/Linux.

**What to implement:**
```
apps/api/backends/           [NEW DIRECTORY]
├── __init__.py              # Protocol/ABC + auto-detect
├── mlx_backend.py           # MLX-native Qwen3-TTS
├── pytorch_backend.py       # Current CUDA path
└── platform_detect.py       # Detect MLX vs PyTorch
```

- Use `mlx-community/Qwen3-TTS-12Hz-1.7B-Base-bf16` model for MLX
- Native Metal acceleration via Apple's Neural Engine
- Auto-detect platform at startup

**Impact:** 4-5x faster inference on Mac. Opens up entire Mac user market.

