## 🟢 MEDIUM-PRIORITY Improvements

### 11. Stories/DAW Timeline Editor

VoiceBox has a full DAW-like story editor with: split, trim, move, duplicate, reorder, multi-track composition, timecode-based mixing, and audio export. Resound has basic podcast scripts only.

### 12. Generation History with Full Metadata

VoiceBox stores complete generation history with search, filtering, stats, and re-generation. Resound has basic history but lacks search and re-generation.

### 13. Audio Channels / Routing

VoiceBox can route voice profiles to specific OS audio devices. Useful for live streaming and podcast production.

### 14. Whisper Transcription

VoiceBox has built-in Whisper transcription with auto-download. Resound doesn't have transcription.

### 15. Profile Avatars

VoiceBox supports avatar images for voice profiles with upload, processing, and display.

### 16. Seed Control for Reproducibility

VoiceBox passes `seed` parameter to generation for reproducible results. Resound's Qwen engine doesn't expose seed control.

### 17. Instruct Mode

VoiceBox supports Qwen3-TTS instruct mode for fine-grained delivery control. Resound has emotion presets but no raw instruct passthrough.

### 18. Model Size Switching

VoiceBox can dynamically switch between 1.7B and 0.6B models mid-session. Resound has this but the implementation is complex due to multi-engine management.

---

## 🔵 POLISH Improvements

### 19. Remove SoX Dependency
Use `librosa` + `soundfile` instead of SoX for audio resampling. Eliminates the external SoX binary requirement.

### 20. Remove FFmpeg Dependency (or Make Optional)
Use `pydub` for format conversion or handle everything in-memory with soundfile.

### 21. Tauri Desktop App (Replace Next.js for Desktop)
If targeting desktop users, Tauri (Rust) provides 10x smaller bundles and native performance vs a browser-based Next.js app.

### 22. SQLite Auto-Migrations
VoiceBox auto-runs migrations in [_run_migrations()](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/backend/database.py#169-290) on startup. No Alembic CLI required.

### 23. RFC 5987 Safe Content-Disposition Headers
VoiceBox handles non-ASCII filenames properly in downloads. Important for international voice names.

### 24. Temp File Cleanup
[qwen_engine.py](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/Resound-Studio/apps/api/engines/qwen_engine.py) [clone_voice()](file:///e:/Code%20Projects/voicebox/Resound-Studio/apps/api/engines/base_engine.py#51-54) creates temp files but cleanup is in a `finally` block that could still leak. Use `contextlib.ExitStack` or proper temp file management.

### 25. LRU Engine Cache Improvements
Current `max_loaded_models=2` is configurable but VRAM detection is missing. Auto-detect available VRAM and set the limit dynamically.

